    <string name="perm_accessibility">Clipboard capture (accessibility)</string>
    <string name="hint_push_requires_accessibility">Android blocks background clipboard reads. Enabling the accessibility service lets the app capture text, images, and files from other apps and push them to the server. Pull works without it. Binary push (image/file) requires accessibility (Shizuku currently pushes text only).</string>
    <string name="perm_shizuku">Shizuku (advanced keep-alive)</string>
    <string name="hint_shizuku_active">Shizuku is active. It applies Doze-whitelist keep-alive and can read clipboard text in the background. For image push, enable the accessibility service as well.</string>
